<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-278-708  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 278 708.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  March 15 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Digital to eliminate 620 jobs at Phoenix, AZ facility. (DigitalEquipment Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Equipment Corp. (personnel management).andO;Ticker:    DEC.andO;Topic:     Computer industryPersonnel ManagementStrategic PlanningPlant ShutdownsReorganization.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>DIGITAL TO ELIMINATE 620 JOBS AT PHOENIX, AZ FACILITY MAYNARD, MASSACHUSETTS, U.S.A., 1990 MAR 13 (NB) -- Digital Equipment Corporation hasannounced that it will halt high- volume manufacturing of terminals, printersand complete computer systems at its Phoenix, AZ plant.andP;  The conversion ofthe plant to a non-manufacturing customer support services facility willresult in the displacement of 620 employees who will be offered an optionalseverance package.andM;The announcement follows closely on the heels of Digital's Mar. 9announcement that it may, in the fiscal quarter ending Mar.31, lose money forthe first time in the firm's 32 year history.andP;  The severance option, whichDigital refers to as &quot;a financial support option,&quot; will provide for a minimumof 40 weeks salary for those with two years or less of service and will rangeas high as two years salary for those with greater seniority.andP;  The plan, tobe offered to all 540 manufacturing employees at the plant and 80 employeesat Digital's western distribution center, also provides continuation ofmedical, dental and life insurance benefits for one year.andP;  Further, Digitalstates that it will provide help in finding jobs for those who accept theoption.andM;This announcement is the first step in Digital's attempt to reduce itsworkforce of approximately 125,000 by 5 to 10 thousand.andP;  Firm spokespersonNiki Richardson was quoted as saying: &quot;We expect 30 to 50 percent will accept[the option].&quot;andP;  She added that those who choose not to take the financialsupport option will have other possible choices including the transfer tosimilar jobs at other Digital facilities or retraining for other Digitalpositions in Phoenix.andM;Kenneth Olson, Digital's president, speaking to an investment conference saidthat the firm's activities to redeploy some US workers and offer severancepackages to others will continue for several months.andP;  In a statement quotedin a published source, Olson said that Digital is analyzing its U.S.andO;operations business by business, &quot;because we don't want to lose the wrongpeople.&quot; He went on to point out that the profitability problems currentlybeing encountered by Digital are the result of industry softness in thedomestic market and are not present in the firm's international business.andP;  Hesaid: &quot;Business is very good in Japan and Europe, and terrible in thiscountry.andP;  We're just fortunate to have the rest of the world to support us.&quot;andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19900314)</TEXT></DOC>